{"word":"ἑτέρωσε","slug":"ἑτέρωσε","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἑτέρωσε</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕτερος'><el>ἕτερος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>to the other side</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:— <i>on one side</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in pregnant sense with Verbs of Rest, as if for <el>ἑτέρωθι</el>, <i>on the other side</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:ἄλλοσε'><el>ἄλλοσε</el></a>, <i>elsewhither</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}